# Cursor AI Rules — TikTok Engagement Engine

## Project overview
Full-stack React (Vite) + Node/Express app that wraps a Python ML engine.
The Python engine lives in `tiktok_engine/` (sibling to this `tiktok-web/` folder).

## File structure
```
tiktok-web/
  client/           ← Vite + React + Tailwind + Recharts
    src/
      pages/        ← Home, Predict, Dashboard, HashtagAnalyzer, Metrics
      components/   ← Layout (nav), UI (shared atoms)
      hooks/        ← useApi (generic fetch hook)
      lib/          ← api.js (all fetch calls to /api/*)
  server/           ← Node/Express
    routes/         ← predict.js, dashboard.js, hashtags.js, metrics.js
    index.js        ← entry, middleware, mounts routes
```

## Key conventions
- All API calls go through `client/src/lib/api.js` — never fetch directly in components
- Use `useApi(fetcher, deps)` hook for data loading — it handles loading/error state
- Tailwind custom tokens: `signal` (red #FE2C55), `cyan-tik` (#69C9D0), `ink` (dark bg)
- Font classes: `font-display` (Syne), `font-body` (DM Sans), `font-mono` (DM Mono)
- Shared atoms: `<Loading>`, `<ErrorState>`, `<StatCard>`, `<MockBadge>`, `<SectionHeader>` from `components/UI.jsx`
- When routes call Python, they fall back to mock data if the model isn't trained yet

## Adding a new page
1. Create `client/src/pages/NewPage.jsx`
2. Add route in `App.jsx`
3. Add nav entry in `components/Layout.jsx` NAV array
4. Add API method in `lib/api.js`
5. Add Express route in `server/routes/`
6. Mount route in `server/index.js`

## Running locally
```bash
# Root
npm run install:all
npm run dev         # starts both client (:5173) and server (:3001)
```

## Connecting the Python ML engine
Set `ML_ROOT` in `server/.env` to the repo root where `models/` and `runs/` live.
The server calls `python3 scripts/predict_cli.py` via execFile.
If the model isn't trained yet, all routes return realistic mock data automatically.
